medical_history.chief_complaint: Periumbilical to right lower quadrant (RLQ) pain.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient was in her usual state of health until 10pm the night prior to presentation when she developed worsening periumbilical pain, which later progressed to RLQ pain. She also experienced worsening nausea and non-bilious non-bloody vomiting. She presented to the ED for evaluation with continued nausea, and denied fevers, chills, diarrhea, sweats, recent weight loss, bright red blood per rectum, melena, chest pain, and shortness of breath.
